# Branch Naming Conventions

## Pattern

```
<type>/<ticket-id>-<short-description>
```

When no ticket exists:

```
<type>/<short-description>
```

## Branch Types

| Type | Purpose | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| `feature` | New functionality | `feature/AUTH-42-oauth-login` |
| `bugfix` | Bug repair | `bugfix/API-99-null-response-crash` |
| `hotfix` | Urgent production fix | `hotfix/DB-7-connection-leak` |
| `release` | Release preparation | `release/2.4.0` |
| `chore` | Tooling, config, maintenance | `chore/update-ci-pipeline` |
| `docs` | Documentation only | `docs/api-usage-guide` |
| `refactor` | Code restructuring | `refactor/extract-validation-module` |
| `test` | Test additions | `test/add-auth-edge-cases` |
| `experiment` | Spikes, prototypes | `experiment/graphql-federation` |

## Rules

- Use lowercase only
- Use hyphens (`-`) as word separators, never underscores or spaces
- Use forward slash (`/`) only to separate type from description
- Keep the description under 50 characters
- Total branch name must not exceed 100 characters
- Include the ticket ID when one exists (e.g., JIRA, GitHub issue number)
- Be descriptive: the name should convey what the branch does

## Validation Regex

```regex
^(feature|bugfix|hotfix|release|chore|docs|refactor|test|experiment)\/[a-z0-9][a-z0-9\-]*[a-z0-9]$
```

## Examples

### Good

```
feature/AUTH-42-add-oauth-provider
bugfix/CART-15-fix-quantity-overflow
hotfix/PROD-3-patch-sql-injection
release/3.1.0
chore/upgrade-spring-boot-3.3
docs/update-deployment-guide
```

### Bad

```
my-branch              # Missing type prefix
feature/My_Branch      # Uppercase and underscores
fix stuff              # Spaces, no type separator
feature/               # Missing description
feature/a-very-long-branch-name-that-goes-on-and-on-about-nothing # Too long, too vague
FEATURE/add-login      # Uppercase type
feature/add_login      # Underscores in description
```

## Special Branches

These branches do not follow the type prefix pattern:

| Branch | Purpose | Protection |
|--------|---------|------------|
| `main` | Production-ready code | Protected, requires PR |
| `develop` | Integration branch (if using GitFlow) | Protected, requires PR |
| `staging` | Pre-production testing | Protected |
